                <h1>Stopping Background Tasks: Understanding the Task Host</h1>
                <p>When a task host is stopping background tasks, it typically indicates system resource management to enhance performance. Background processes are paused to allocate memory and CPU resources effectively, ensuring critical tasks run smoothly. This helps maintain overall system efficiency and user experience while preventing potential overloads.</p>
